Version Identifiers

  • A client must be able to propose a version identifier to be used for a new member of a version graph.

  • The server may refuse to use the client's suggested version identifier.

  • The server should tell the client what version identifier it has assigned to the new member of the version graph.

  • A version identifier must be unique across a version graph.
